OL,3,CWhy zero net migration may not be
OL,4,Cpossible or desirable
OL,6,FOverall population growth in the UK,
OL,7,Fmuch of which is down to immigration,
OL,8,Fhas also outpaced the number of . This
OL,9,Fhas probably put upward pressure on
OL,10,Fproperty prices.
OL,12,FMore clearly, public services in some
OL,13,Fparts of the UK have also struggled to
OL,14,Frespond to sharp increases in demand,
OL,15,Fwhether that's access to GP care or
OL,16,Fschool places.
OL,18,Fto the above is to reduce net
OL,19,Fmigration to zero.
