OL,3,CWhy zero net migration may not be
OL,4,Cpossible or desirable
OL,6,FThe most obvious challenge with such a
OL,7,Fpledge is delivering on it is much,
OL,8,Fmuch harder than it sounds.
OL,10,FYou are essentially promising to
OL,11,Fbalance the number of people arriving
OL,12,Fin the UK each year with the number
OL,13,Fleaving. And you only have control of
OL,14,Fthe number of people arriving.
OL,16,F"Zero Net Migration" isn't that
OL,17,Fdifferent to David Cameron's pledge in
OL,18,F2010 to reduce net migration to the
OL,19,F"tens of thousands".
