OL,3,CWhy zero net migration may not be
OL,4,Cpossible or desirable
OL,6,FHis government failed to do it and
OL,7,Fsuffered enormous damage to its
OL,8,Freputation as a result.
OL,10,FConceivably, Cameron's government
OL,11,Fcould have come closer to hitting the
OL,12,Ftarget than it did but ultimately it
OL,13,Fdecided that doing so would have
OL,14,Fcreated a set of other problems that
OL,15,Fvoters probably wouldn't be prepared
OL,16,Fto accept - not least a deterioration
OL,17,Fin public services.
