OL,3,CWhy zero net migration may not be
OL,4,Cpossible or desirable
OL,6,FThe evidence collected by The
OL,7,FMigration Observatory, of the
OL,8,FUniversity of Oxford, shows that
OL,9,Fmigrants are less likely to be
OL,10,Funemployed than people born in the UK
OL,11,Fand less likely to claim unemployment
OL,12,Fbenefits if they are.
OL,14,FMigrants workers are often well
OL,15,Feducated and, compared with those born
OL,16,Fin the UK, are more likely to work in
OL,17,Fjobs for which they are overqualified.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G9/15
