OL,3,CWhy zero net migration may not be
OL,4,Cpossible or desirable
OL,6,FThe government's economic forecaster,
OL,7,Fthe Office for Budget Responsibility
OL,8,F(OBR), says higher net migration
OL,9,Freduces pressure on servicing the
OL,10,Fgovernment's debt over time.
OL,12,FThe logic is that migrants are more
OL,13,Flikely to be of working age and
OL,14,Ftherefore more likely to be paying tax
OL,15,Fand contributing to the public
OL,16,Ffinances.
