OL,3,CWhy zero net migration may not be
OL,4,Cpossible or desirable
OL,6,FThe OBR is more cautious about the
OL,7,Fimpact on overall living standards.
OL,8,FHigher net migration "has been a key
OL,9,Fdriver of economic growth in recent
OL,10,Fyears", it concludes but "may not have
OL,11,Fa substantial impact on output per
OL,12,Fperson".
OL,14,FIn end care, when we think of measures
OL,15,Fof our economic prosperity, we should
OL,16,Fcare more about Gross Domestic Product
OL,17,FPer Capita (per person) than aggregate
OL,18,FGDP.
