OL,4,Cpossible or desirable
OL,6,FAnd GDP per person is not necessarily
OL,7,Fimproved by having more people in a
OL,8,Fcountry. If you increase the number of
OL,9,Fpeople by 10% and the economy grows by
OL,10,F10% then on an individual basis no one
OL,11,Fis better off.
OL,13,FThe evidence shows that migrants have
OL,14,Fbeen coming to the UK to work and, by
OL,15,Fand large, .
