OL,3,CWhy zero net migration may not be
OL,4,Cpossible or desirable
OL,6,FToday, the UK has a low rate of
OL,7,Funemployment and, in recent years,
OL,8,Fthere has been an increase in the
OL,9,Fnumber of organisations in the public
OL,10,Fand private sector complaining they
OL,11,Fcan't get the staff they need.
OL,13,FThe government has tried to solve this
OL,14,Fproblem domestically.
OL,16,FIt has sought to reduce low-skilled
OL,17,Fmigration, arguing there are people
OL,18,Fliving in Britain who could and should
OL,19,Fbe filling vacancies.
